##The first snow in Shanghai in 2020 was warmer than usual

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

The paper, Li Jiawei, Chen Si, reporter trainee, Zhang Hui

The Wind, rain and snow are falling, and the cold wave is hitting Shanghai.

It was the strongest cold wave since 2020. Shanghai epidemic prevention and control non-stop, many people adhere to the cold night, guard Shanghai, will wind and snow ginger tea drink together.

From 10 pm to midnight on February 15, the reporter of the www.thepaper.cn  interviewed the night watchmen who had entered Hudaokou, communities and hospitals to witness the first snowfall, and their commitment to the mission and honor of fighting the epidemic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At about 2230 hours on February 15, public security police, health and epidemic prevention personnel and auxiliary police at Zhuqiao Public Security checkpoint were inspecting the driveway. Zou Qiaotu, reporter, thepaper.cn

Zhuqiao public security checkpoint: The first snow, guard into the Shanghai Pass

After 23:00, Shanghai "northwest Gateway" G15 High-speed Zhuqiao Public Security Checkpoint, Snow beads gradually into a large snowflake, falling from the sky, shuttling traffic into Shanghai to accept registration inspection.

From 5 pm on that day, Jiading District Public Security Bureau Jiacheng police station to reinforce Daokou Police Shen Xin has been on the Daokou Inspection Post, he will continue to work until 8 am the next day.

At this time, another big truck drove into the face. "please wear a mask and show your identity card, " Shen Xin went up to check the driver's and co-driver's identity card, next to the health and anti-epidemic personnel with the forehead temperature gun on the two men.

The driver, Mr. Lu, reported the situation. The two of them came from Lingbi County, Anhui Province. They pulled 3,000 boxes of gloves on the car and transported them to a unit in Hangtou town, Pudong New Area. After unloading, the empty car was ready to return by the same road again without stopping in Shanghai.

Shen instructed them to fill in information on the health cloud. At present, every person entering Shanghai must fill in the health information. Fill in the phone will receive a verification code, equivalent to a "customs documents. ". Mr. Lu qualified, he jumped back in the car to roll down the window, again waving to the police.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 15, Mr. Hu delivered goods from Lingbi County, Anhui Province to Hangtou town, Pudong, Shanghai, and registered his information at Zhuqiao public security checkpoint. By Li Jiawei, _ thepaper_news

"The snow day drives slowly, safe all the way. " The car starts steadily, Shen Xin says and walks to the next car.

The ZHUQIAO CHECKPOINT HAS 8 lanes and 2 truck lanes, each of which is equipped with police, auxiliary police, medical staff and volunteers. Strict inspections are carried out 24 hours for every vehicle entering Shanghai. Reporters observed that although most of the vehicles and personnel meet the conditions, there are also the scene was persuaded to return.

At 23:00, hanging Zhejiang b license plate Mr. Yu was led to the review point, he confessed that he did not live in Shanghai and work. He was driving from his hometown in Cixi City, Zhejiang Province, to his destination in Taicang, Jiangsu Province, where he was told he could not enter. He tried to return to Cixi City by way of Shanghai and was stopped at the Zhuqiao checkpoint.

"Just negotiated with the police, I can not enter Shanghai, but fortunately this side of the police to help me guide to another can go back to Zhejiang highway. " Night cold heart warm, Mr. Yu said he was extremely grateful.

By the time it got around midnight on February 16, the snow was already falling harder and harder, hurting his face. He Xiaofeng, a police officer at the Zhuqiao checkpoint, said they were issued warm baby protection against the cold, cotton-padded clothes are also very warm, the canteen is also prepared ginger soup, standing at the entrance of the road is not afraid of the cold.

"At this critical time in the fight against the epidemic, we will check every vehicle and every person, and the suspects will not miss a single one, " he said. No matter what kind of bad weather, the primary responsibility is to stand guard and guard the entrance to Shanghai.

After zero, the lower the temperature, the police began to check the road conditions around the junction. Once found frozen and snow conditions, will immediately snow and ice removal and road personnel to ensure the safety of pedestrians and vehicles.

As of 2400 hours on February 15, the Zhuqiao public security checkpoint had inspected 8,503 vehicles and 19,226 people throughout the day, of which 52 vehicles and 89 people had been persuaded to return. One person was found to have fever symptoms on the same day and was transferred to the designated fever clinic for medical treatment. The other 2 persons were transported to the central isolation point in the same vehicle for medical observation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A family of three late at night from the field to return to Shanghai, at the community gate registration, paper news reporter, Cao Junjie Map

Under the Glittering Days, protected by them

Dozens of kilometers away from Zhuqiao, Kangtai new city, located in Baoshan District of Shanghai, has no flakes of snow, and dense ice grains keep falling.

More than 10 pm, security season to see, although more ice, but hit the PUDDLE, quickly melt. According to the cell phone, the temperature is close to freezing.

The entrance of the community with an umbrella, the surrounding with a tarp as a shelter. Under the wind and rain, umbrella top and the ground have water, the rain cloth was also ripped Shua sound.

Shed, old season drink ginger tea to add energy, "ginger cut into slices, their own boil, " he should be on duty until 12 o'clock, and then by the night shift of two colleagues to replace. The returning security guards could not return for the time being, and the epidemic prevention work required more manpower. Everyone began to work overtime, basically two shifts.

Property Manager Guo Bing is also in, old season said, special period, managers shift duty during the day, late at night also often come to see.

Guo Bing told reporters that now is the first two days of the implementation of the pass system, some residents do not adapt, more than a few people on duty to explain, but also at any time to coordinate the conflict that may occur.

When a resident said not yet, Guo Bing let people sign in duplicate letter of commitment, urged it to hurry up, otherwise can not release the second time.

With more than 3,000 households and tens of thousands of people, Kangtai new town is one of the largest communities in Dachang town, with a perimeter of more than three kilometers.

During the cold spell, few people came in and out, and occasionally residents came out to get takeout. When a family of three pull a suitcase to walk, old season and Guo Bing are alert, after checking identity, registration, temperature, three people into the community.

For Lu Tonggang, General Secretary of the Party branch of CANT's new town, the evenings were spent working online.

His wechat, the owner group, party members, town-level prevention and Control Group and more than 20 working groups, from time to time there are news pop-up. Speaking to the reporter, the mask group has new information, the second round of mask registration has started, on the number of masks, arrival time, he wants to maintain communication with the pharmacy.

In addition to day-to-day prevention and control, the residents also have an important task, that is, to guard the psychological defense line of the residents.

Lu Tonggang said that two days ago, there are staff wearing protective clothing in the community disinfection, photos quickly spread across the owners, residents have asked, "is there a confirmed diagnosis? " At this time, the need to explain the neighborhood.

Shortly before 11 o'clock, Lu Tonggang and Guo bing were on patrol again. The Path was dark, but when I looked up, I saw Glittering Days.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 0Am on February 16, nurse Zheng Jiawen went to work in the observation room of the isolation ward. Image courtesy of the BBC

Hot Air coming in hot

The cold wind beat against the window, and some people did not feel the cold at all, but shouted "Hot" .

At 11:30 pm, braving the cold wind, nurse Zheng Jiawen arrived at the isolation ward building of Xinhua Hospital affiliated to Shanghai Jiaotong University Medical College half an hour early. After reporting to the head nurse, she put on a heavy isolation suit and entered the isolation ward observation room with another colleague. They work from 0 a.m. to 8 a.m. , during which time they can not drink water, eat or go to the bathroom.

The residents, all suspected cases of new pneumonia, had to go through two 24-hour viral nucleic acid tests, both negative, which means each suspected case would have to be here for at least 48 hours.

Carrying out nursing treatment and taking care of patients'daily life is Zheng Jiawen's key work. In addition, she also has to complete the disinfection and cleaning of the isolation ward. She keeps toothpaste, toothbrushes, towels and other supplies ready for new cases as soon as they arrive, and cleans up after them if a patient leaves.

After 12 a.m. , Zheng begins the process, which she repeats every two hours, carefully sterilizing everything from air to surfaces, computer keyboards, phones, desk tops to door knobs.

While she disinfects, she also keeps an eye on patients on intravenous drip in the ward, monitoring their basic vital signs.

Just busy for a while, she heard a ringing, "nurse, hot water? " This is the call of a mother in the observation room, she wanted to help the child to drink hot water, Zheng Jiawen immediately poured water to the ward.

About 15 minutes. The decontamination process is complete. She also had to keep an eye out for the convenient toilets that patients could take out of the door of the ward at any time. Since patients could not leave their own ward under isolation, the hospital had prepared such toilets for everyone, disinfection and handling of patients'stool and urine has also become a part of Zheng Jiawen's work.

Though it was 2 a.m. , Zheng and her colleagues were busy. In order to keep the air flowing, the isolation ward must not be air conditioning, and the windows must be opened to ensure ventilation.

It was cold air; Zheng Jiawen could feel no cold at all. In the ward to walk up and down, over and over disinfection work down, protective clothing in her only feel stuffy, constantly sweating.

In view of the cold spell, the hospital has arranged 11 heaters and four oil heaters in the ward and office area, but Zheng Jiawen shouted "hot" , which she hardly needed this night.
